The '''bottom eta meson''' ({{Subatomic particle|Bottom Eta}}) or '''eta-b meson''' is a [[flavour (particle physics)|flavourless]] [[meson]] formed from a [[bottom quark]] and its [[antiparticle]]. It was first observed by the [[BaBar experiment]] at [[SLAC]] in 2008, and is the lightest particle containing a bottom and anti-bottom quark.
